criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Chart diagnosis of schizophrenia, schizoaffective disorder, bipolar disorder, or major
             depressive disorder;

          2. 18 years or older;

          3. A rating of "3" or higher on one of three Patient Activation items;

          4. Ownership of a mobile phone with call/text plan (research staff will offer assistance
             in accessing the Federal Lifeline Assistance Program to people who do not have a
             mobile phone and/or call/text plan if they are otherwise eligible);

          5. Receiving community based treatment services.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Hearing, vision, or motor impairment that make it impossible to operate a mobile phone
             (determined using the individual's device for screening);

          2. English reading level below 4th grade (determined using the reading section from the
             Wide Range Achievement Test - 4th Edition (WRAT-4).
